% Arithmetic assumptions on the left of `=>` (BETA spec section 2.3).
% A comparison/presburger fact assumed by a local implication is an
% antecedent for any `presburger` goal in its scope: the goal succeeds
% iff (assumptions => goal) holds. A goal entailed by the assumptions is
% discharged (not retained as a residual). Without this, the assumption
% was ignored and `pi C\ (C > 3 => presburger "C > 1")` wrongly failed.
%
% Expected:
%   ?- pi C\ (C > 3 => presburger "C > 1").   => yes.  (C>3 entails C>1)
%   ?- pi C\ (C > 3 => presburger "C > 5").   => no.   (C=4 counterexample)
%   ?- (1 > 3) => presburger "5 > 100".       => yes.  (false antecedent)
%   ?- pi C\ (C > 3 => presburger "C + 1 > 4"). => yes. (decomposed goal)
